&dpr=1','{}',4,'true','/blog/vue-js-experimental-vapor-mode','{"title":"[Vue][November 2024] - Introducing Vue’s latest experimental Vapor Mode","description":"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"}','blog/003.vue-js-experimental-vapor-mode','rIfjlH8jgzU2VGF9T60NIow2X6sf_lbSD8mBOrCPVcg');
INSERT INTO "_content_blog" VALUES('blog/blog/004.ecma-script-2024-nears-finalization.md','[Javascript][December 2024] - ECMAScript 2024 Nears Finalization','{"name":"Sean Erick C. Ramones","avatar":{"src":"avatars/profile-image-1.png","alt":"Sean Erick C. Ramones"}}','{"type":"minimark","value":[["h1",{"id":"javascriptdecember-2024-ecmascript-2024-nears-finalization"},"[Javascript]",["span",{},"December 2024"]," - ECMAScript 2024 Nears Finalization"],["p",{},["em",{},"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"]],["h2",{"id":"introduction"},["strong",{},"Introduction"]],["p",{},"As the foundation of JavaScript, ECMAScript continues to evolve to meet the demands of modern application development. Each year, the ECMAScript specification introduces new features that enhance developer productivity, improve performance, and simplify common tasks. In 2024, ECMAScript is set to release its next major update, bringing powerful new capabilities to the JavaScript language. This report highlights the key features in ",["strong",{},"ECMAScript 2024"],", their impact, and what developers can expect as the finalization of this standard nears."],["h2",{"id":"key-features-in-ecmascript-2024"},["strong",{},"Key Features in ECMAScript 2024"]],["p",{},"The following are the most anticipated features in the upcoming ECMAScript 2024 release:"],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Array Grouping"],"\nThe new ",["code",{},"groupBy"]," and ",["code",{},"groupByToMap"]," methods make it significantly easier to group array elements based on a specified criterion. This eliminates the need for custom logic when transforming array data.",["br",{}],["strong",{},"Example:"],["pre",{"className":["language-text"],"code":"const data = [\n  { name: ''Alice'', category: ''A'' },\n  { name: ''Bob'', category: ''B'' },\n  { name: ''Charlie'', category: ''A'' }\n];\n\nconst grouped = Object.groupBy(data, item => item.category);\nconsole.log(grouped);\n// Output:\n// {\n//   A: [ { name: ''Alice'', category: ''A'' }, { name: ''Charlie'', category: ''A'' } ],\n//   B: [ { name: ''Bob'', category: ''B'' } ]\n// }\n","language":"text"},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},"const data = [\n  { name: ''Alice'', category: ''A'' },\n  { name: ''Bob'', category: ''B'' },\n  { name: ''Charlie'', category: ''A'' }\n];\n\nconst grouped = Object.groupBy(data, item => item.category);\nconsole.log(grouped);\n// Output:\n// {\n//   A: [ { name: ''Alice'', category: ''A'' }, { name: ''Charlie'', category: ''A'' } ],\n//   B: [ { name: ''Bob'', category: ''B'' } ]\n// }\n"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Why It Matters"],": This feature simplifies data manipulation tasks that were previously verbose and error-prone."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Symbols as WeakMap Keys"],"\nTo understand this feature, it''s helpful to first understand ",["strong",{},"symbols"]," in JavaScript. A ",["em",{},"symbol"]," is a unique, immutable data type that is often used as an object key. Unlike strings, every symbol is completely unique, even if it has the same description.",["br",{}],["strong",{},"Example:"],["pre",{"className":["language-text"],"code":"const sym1 = Symbol(''key'');\nconst sym2 = Symbol(''key'');\nconsole.log(sym1 === sym2); // false (they are unique)\n","language":"text"},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},"const sym1 = Symbol(''key'');\nconst sym2 = Symbol(''key'');\nconsole.log(sym1 === sym2); // false (they are unique)\n"]],["br",{}],"Symbols are often used to avoid key collisions in objects, making them useful for scenarios where unique keys are essential.",["br",{}],"WeakMaps allow objects to be used as keys without preventing garbage collection, meaning objects can be removed from memory when no longer needed. With ECMAScript 2024, ",["strong",{},"symbols can now serve as keys in WeakMaps"],", combining the uniqueness of symbols with the memory efficiency of WeakMaps.",["br",{}],["strong",{},"Example:"],["pre",{"className":"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"const mySymbol = Symbol(''myKey'');\nconst weakMap = new WeakMap();\nconst obj = {};\n\nweakMap.set(mySymbol, ''value'');\nconsole.log(weakMap.has(mySymbol)); // true\n","language":"jsx","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{"class":"spNyl"},"const"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," mySymbol "],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"="],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"}," Symbol"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"("],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"myKey"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{"class":"spNyl"},"const"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," weakMap "],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"="],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," new"],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"}," WeakMap"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"()"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{"class":"spNyl"},"const"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," obj "],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"="],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {};\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":4},["span",{"emptyLinePlaceholder":true},"\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":5},["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"weakMap"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"set"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(mySymbol"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"value"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":6},["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"console"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"log"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(weakMap"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"has"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(mySymbol))"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";"],["span",{"class":"sHwdD"}," // true\n"]]]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Why It Matters"],": Previously, WeakMaps could only use objects as keys. Allowing symbols as keys makes WeakMaps more versatile, particularly in cases where symbols are preferred for their uniqueness and immutability."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Improved ",["code",{},"Object.hasOwn"]],"\nThe ",["code",{},"Object.hasOwn"]," method, introduced in ECMAScript 2022, simplifies property checks. ECMAScript 2024 refines its behavior for better ergonomics and performance when checking an object''s own properties.",["br",{}],["strong",{},"Example:"],["pre",{"className":"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"const obj = { name: ''Alice'' };\nconsole.log(Object.hasOwn(obj, ''name'')); // true\nconsole.log(Object.hasOwn(obj, ''age''));  // false\n","language":"jsx","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{"class":"spNyl"},"const"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," obj "],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"="],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," name"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"Alice"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," };\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"console"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"log"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(Object"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"hasOwn"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(obj"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"name"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"))"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";"],["span",{"class":"sHwdD"}," // true\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"console"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"log"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(Object"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"hasOwn"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"(obj"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"age"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"))"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";"],["span",{"class":"sHwdD"},"  // false\n"]]]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Why It Matters"],": This provides a clearer and more reliable way to check for direct properties compared to ",["code",{},"hasOwnProperty"],"."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Extended Error Cause"],"\nThe ",["code",{},"cause"]," property in error objects enables developers to provide additional context when throwing errors. ECMAScript 2024 extends this capability, improving debugging and error handling.",["br",{}],["strong",{},"Example:"],["pre",{"className":"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"try {\n  throw new Error(''Failed to connect to database'');\n} catch (err) {\n  throw new Error(''Application failed'', { cause: err });\n}\n","language":"jsx","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{"class":"s7zQu"},"try"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{"class":"s7zQu"},"  throw"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," new"],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"}," Error"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"("],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"Failed to connect to database"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"}"],["span",{"class":"s7zQu"}," catch"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," (err) "],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"{\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":4},["span",{"class":"s7zQu"},"  throw"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," new"],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"}," Error"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"("],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"Application failed"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," cause"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," err"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," }"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":5},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"}\n"]]]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Why It Matters"],": This improves error traceability, particularly in large codebases and complex workflows."]]]],["hr",{}],["h2",{"id":"impact-of-ecmascript-2024"},["strong",{},"Impact of ECMAScript 2024"]],["p",{},"The new features in ECMAScript 2024 are designed to:"],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Simplify Code"],": Features like array grouping reduce boilerplate code and improve readability, making JavaScript cleaner and easier to maintain."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Enhance Performance"],": Refinements like ",["code",{},"Object.hasOwn"]," and the extended use of symbols improve the overall efficiency of JavaScript operations."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Improve Developer Experience"],": Enhanced error handling with the ",["code",{},"cause"]," property provides better debugging insights, saving developers time during troubleshooting."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Strengthen Modern Applications"],": Features like WeakMap symbol support align with advanced use cases in memory-sensitive and modular application designs."]],["p",{},"As developers adopt ECMAScript 2024, they can expect a more streamlined and powerful experience when working with JavaScript, further cementing its role as the go-to language for web development."],["hr",{}],["h2",{"id":"adopting-ecmascript-2024"},["strong",{},"Adopting ECMAScript 2024"]],["p",{},"To leverage the features in ECMAScript 2024, developers should:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Stay up-to-date with modern runtimes like ",["strong",{},"Node.js"],", ",["strong",{},"Deno"],", and browser engines such as ",["strong",{},"V8"]," and ",["strong",{},"SpiderMonkey"],", which are expected to integrate the updates soon after finalization."],["li",{},"Use ",["code",{},"transpilers"]," like ",["strong",{},"Babel"]," or tools like ",["strong",{},"esbuild"]," and ",["strong",{},"SWC"]," to enable backward compatibility for environments that do not yet support ECMAScript 2024 natively."],["li",{},"Explore updated documentation and proposals on the ",["a",{"href":"https://github.com/tc39","rel":["nofollow"]},"TC39 GitHub repository"]," to stay informed about final changes."]],["hr",{}],["h2",{"id":"conclusion"},["strong",{},"Conclusion"]],["p",{},"ECMAScript 2024 introduces features that significantly enhance the JavaScript language, making it more powerful, efficient, and developer-friendly. From simplified array grouping to improved error handling, these updates address common challenges and provide tools that streamline modern application development. As finalization nears, developers can look forward to a more productive and performant JavaScript ecosystem, reaffirming JavaScript''s position as the backbone of the web."],["style",{},"html pre.shiki code .spNyl, html code.shiki .spNyl{--shiki-light:#9C3EDA;--shiki-default:#C792EA;--shiki-dark:#C792EA}html pre.shiki code .sTEyZ, html code.shiki .sTEyZ{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-default:#EEFFFF;--shiki-dark:#BABED8}html pre.shiki code .sMK4o, html code.shiki .sMK4o{--shiki-light:#39ADB5;--shiki-default:#89DDFF;--shiki-dark:#89DDFF}html pre.shiki code .s2Zo4, html code.shiki .s2Zo4{--shiki-light:#6182B8;--shiki-default:#82AAFF;--shiki-dark:#82AAFF}html pre.shiki code .sfazB, html code.shiki .sfazB{--shiki-light:#91B859;--shiki-default:#C3E88D;--shiki-dark:#C3E88D}html pre.shiki code .sHwdD, html code.shiki .sHwdD{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-light-font-style:italic;--shiki-default:#546E7A;--shiki-default-font-style:italic;--shiki-dark:#676E95;--shiki-dark-font-style:italic}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration);}html.dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .swJcz, html code.shiki .swJcz{--shiki-light:#E53935;--shiki-default:#F07178;--shiki-dark:#F07178}html pre.shiki code .s7zQu, html code.shiki .s7zQu{--shiki-light:#39ADB5;--shiki-light-font-style:italic;--shiki-default:#89DDFF;--shiki-default-font-style:italic;--shiki-dark:#89DDFF;--shiki-dark-font-style:italic}"]],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"introduction","depth":2,"text":"Introduction"},{"id":"key-features-in-ecmascript-2024","depth":2,"text":"Key Features in ECMAScript 2024"},{"id":"impact-of-ecmascript-2024","depth":2,"text":"Impact of ECMAScript 2024"},{"id":"adopting-ecmascript-2024","depth":2,"text":"Adopting ECMAScript 2024"},{"id":"conclusion","depth":2,"text":"Conclusion"}]}}','2024-12-01T00:00:00.000Z','By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME','md','https://images.pexels.com/photos/4955393/pexels-photo-4955393.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1','{}',4,'true','/blog/ecma-script-2024-nears-finalization','{"title":"[Javascript][December 2024] - ECMAScript 2024 Nears Finalization","description":"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"}','blog/004.ecma-script-2024-nears-finalization','ooN_ULCT6pV2bi-k0kFvZ2eGgzKCNefYprW0TqqQTbc');
INSERT INTO "_content_blog" VALUES('blog/blog/005.ui-libraries-for-vuejs.md','[Vue][December 2024] - UI Libraries for VueJS: Vuetify, Tailwind, and PrimeVue','{"name":"Sean Erick C. Ramones","avatar":{"src":"avatars/profile-image-1.png","alt":"Sean Erick C. Ramones"}}','{"type":"minimark","value":[["h1",{"id":"vuedecember-2024-ui-libraries-for-vuejs-vuetify-tailwind-and-primevue"},"[Vue]",["span",{},"December 2024"]," - UI Libraries for VueJS: Vuetify, Tailwind, and PrimeVue"],["p",{},["em",{},"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"]],["p",{},"For this month, I’d like to discuss on 3rd party libraries that can help speed up Vue application’s development, using template-ready UI components."],["p",{},"The Vue.js ecosystem has experienced significant growth and diversification, particularly in the realm of component libraries and styling frameworks. These tools are critical for improving developer productivity, ensuring consistency in design systems, and accelerating development workflows. This report highlights the current state of the more popular choices in the ecosystem, focusing on ",["strong",{},"Vuetify"],", ",["strong",{},"Tailwind CSS"],", and ",["strong",{},"PrimeVue"],", three widely adopted tools that cater to different needs within the Vue.js development landscape."],["h3",{"id":"tailwind-css-utility-first-styling-for-modern-applications"},["strong",{},"Tailwind CSS: Utility-First Styling for Modern Applications"]],["p",{},["a",{"href":"https://tailwindcss.com/","rel":["nofollow"]},"Tailwind CSS"]," has revolutionized how developers style Vue.js applications by embracing a utility-first approach. Rather than relying on pre-styled components, Tailwind enables developers to build custom UIs faster by composing small, reusable utility classes."],["h3",{"id":"key-features"},["strong",{},"Key Features"],":"],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Utility-First Design"],": Avoids the need for custom CSS by using pre-defined utility classes."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Highly Customizable"],": Configuration files allow developers to define custom themes, breakpoints, and utilities."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Performance-Oriented"],": Tools like JIT (Just-In-Time) mode reduce unused CSS, ensuring smaller bundle sizes."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Ecosystem Compatibility"],": Tailwind integrates seamlessly with Vue.js templates and single-file components (SFCs)."]],["h3",{"id":"adoption-and-use-cases"},["strong",{},"Adoption and Use Cases"],":"],["p",{},["a",{"href":"https://tailwindcss.com/","rel":["nofollow"]},"Tailwind CSS"]," is particularly suited for:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Projects requiring rapid prototyping with full design control."],["li",{},"Developers who prefer minimal dependency on pre-styled components."],["li",{},"Teams focusing on creating unique and highly customized UIs."]],["h3",{"id":"challenges"},["strong",{},"Challenges"],":"],["ul",{},["li",{},"The learning curve can be steep for beginners unfamiliar with utility-first CSS."],["li",{},"Class-heavy markup may become difficult to manage without tools like ",["strong",{},"Prettier"]," or ",["strong",{},"@apply"]," directives."]],["p",{},"Tailwind’s growing popularity within the Vue ecosystem is a testament to its flexibility and its ability to balance performance with design freedom."],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"primevue-feature-rich-ui-components-for-enterprise-apps"},["strong",{},"PrimeVue: Feature-Rich UI Components for Enterprise Apps"]],["p",{},["a",{"href":"https://primevue.org/","rel":["nofollow"]},"PrimeVue"]," is a rapidly growing component library that provides a rich set of UI components designed for Vue.js applications. Unlike Tailwind, PrimeVue focuses on delivering pre-built components with extensive features, making it an excellent choice for enterprise applications."],["h3",{"id":"key-features-1"},["strong",{},"Key Features"],":"],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Comprehensive Component Suite"],": Offers over 80 components, including advanced data tables, charts, calendars, and tree views."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Theming System"],": Built-in themes and the ability to customize or create new themes."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Accessibility"],": Fully compliant with WAI-ARIA guidelines for accessibility."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Vue 3 Ready"],": PrimeVue is optimized for Vue 3 and provides excellent TypeScript support."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Enterprise Focus"],": Rich features like virtual scrolling, lazy loading, and server-side rendering (SSR) support."]],["h3",{"id":"adoption-and-use-cases-1"},["strong",{},"Adoption and Use Cases"],":"],["p",{},"PrimeVue is ideal for:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Enterprise applications requiring complex UI components like data grids and charts."],["li",{},"Applications that prioritize functionality and feature richness over lightweight builds."],["li",{},"Teams looking for out-of-the-box solutions to accelerate development."]],["h3",{"id":"challenges-1"},["strong",{},"Challenges"],":"],["ul",{},["li",{},"The library may be overkill for small projects or simple UIs."],["li",{},"Applications requiring unique, highly customized designs might find PrimeVue’s pre-styled components limiting."]],["p",{},"PrimeVue’s balance of feature-rich components and modern Vue.js support positions it as a strong competitor to libraries like Vuetify and Element Plus."],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"conclusion"},["strong",{},"Conclusion"]],["p",{},"The Vue.js ecosystem offers a variety of libraries and frameworks to address different needs in modern application development:"],["ul",{},["li",{},["a",{"href":"https://vuetifyjs.com/en/","rel":["nofollow"]},["strong",{},"Vuetify"]]," is a robust solution for Material Design-focused applications."],["li",{},["a",{"href":"https://tailwindcss.com/","rel":["nofollow"]},["strong",{},"Tailwind CSS"]]," provides unparalleled design flexibility with its utility-first approach."],["li",{},["a",{"href":"https://primevue.org/","rel":["nofollow"]},["strong",{},"PrimeVue"]]," delivers enterprise-grade components with rich features and accessibility."]],["p",{},"Each tool caters to different developer preferences and project requirements, and understanding their strengths allows teams to make informed decisions when building Vue.js applications. As Vue continues to evolve, these libraries will remain integral to its ecosystem, driving innovation and improving the developer experience."]],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"tailwind-css-utility-first-styling-for-modern-applications","depth":3,"text":"Tailwind CSS: Utility-First Styling for Modern Applications"},{"id":"key-features","depth":3,"text":"Key Features:"},{"id":"adoption-and-use-cases","depth":3,"text":"Adoption and Use Cases:"},{"id":"challenges","depth":3,"text":"Challenges:"},{"id":"primevue-feature-rich-ui-components-for-enterprise-apps","depth":3,"text":"PrimeVue: Feature-Rich UI Components for Enterprise Apps"},{"id":"key-features-1","depth":3,"text":"Key Features:"},{"id":"adoption-and-use-cases-1","depth":3,"text":"Adoption and Use Cases:"},{"id":"challenges-1","depth":3,"text":"Challenges:"},{"id":"conclusion","depth":3,"text":"Conclusion"}]}}','2024-12-01T00:00:00.000Z','By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME','md','https://images.pexels.com/photos/1181271/pexels-photo-1181271.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1','{}',3,'true','/blog/ui-libraries-for-vuejs','{"title":"[Vue][December 2024] - UI Libraries for VueJS: Vuetify, Tailwind, and PrimeVue","description":"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"}','blog/005.ui-libraries-for-vuejs','pj7CfGYKfsh1X-IwVSxe9inEaHeWmryQwdeIx-Knr4o');
INSERT INTO "_content_blog" VALUES('blog/blog/006.micro-frontend-architecture.md','[Javascript][January 2025] - Micro Frontend Architecture','{"name":"Sean Erick C. Ramones","avatar":{"src":"avatars/profile-image-1.png","alt":"Sean Erick C. Ramones"}}','{"type":"minimark","value":[["h1",{"id":"javascriptjanuary-2025-micro-frontend-architecture"},"[Javascript]",["span",{},"January 2025"]," - Micro Frontend Architecture"],["p",{},["em",{},"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"]],["h2",{"id":"introduction"},["strong",{},"Introduction"]],["p",{},"Micro frontend architecture is a modern web development approach that brings micro-service principles to frontend applications. It breaks down large frontend applications into smaller, independent pieces. Each piece—a \"micro frontend\"—manages a specific part of the user interface, allowing teams to work on different sections of an application independently."],["p",{},["img",{"alt":"image.png","src":"/blog/micro-frontend-architecture-diagram.png"}]],["p",{},"Figure 1: Micro Frontend Architecture Pipeline Diagram showing three independent micro frontends (A, B and C) with their respective source control, build and test pipelines, leading to production deployment where they are composed into a single application."],["h2",{"id":"core-principles"},["strong",{},"Core Principles"]],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Independent Deployment"],": Teams can build, test, and deploy each micro frontend separately, enabling faster updates while reducing the risk of system-wide failures."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Technology Agnostic"],": Teams can choose different frameworks or libraries—React, Vue.js, or others—as long as they follow agreed-upon interface standards."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Team Autonomy"],": Teams gain complete ownership of their segments, leading to better focus and faster development cycles with fewer dependencies."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Isolated Codebases"],": Separate repositories and build pipelines help avoid merge conflicts and simplify codebase maintenance."]],["h2",{"id":"advantages"},["strong",{},"Advantages"]],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Scalability"],": Teams can scale each micro frontend based on specific segment needs."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Faster Time to Market"],": Parallel development and deployment accelerate product delivery."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Improved Maintenance"],": Isolated components make bug fixes and updates more manageable."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Flexibility in Technology Choices"],": Teams can select tools and frameworks that best suit their needs."]],["h2",{"id":"challenges"},["strong",{},"Challenges"]],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Increased Complexity"],": Managing multiple micro frontends adds complexity to integration, deployment, and component communication."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Consistency in UX"],": Maintaining a uniform user experience becomes challenging when teams use different technologies."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Performance Overheads"],": Multiple micro frontends require careful optimization through lazy loading and efficient bundling."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Shared State and Communication"],": Managing shared state and inter-component communication demands thoughtful architecture using event buses or shared services."]],["h2",{"id":"use-cases"},["strong",{},"Use Cases"]],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Large Enterprise Applications"],": Multi-team applications benefit from micro frontend architecture."],["li",{},["strong",{},"E-commerce Platforms"],": Separate teams can manage product pages, cart, and checkout independently."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Content Management Systems (CMS)"],": Teams can develop and maintain different content modules separately."]],["h2",{"id":"best-practices"},["strong",{},"Best Practices"]],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Define Clear Boundaries"],": Each micro frontend should have distinct responsibilities with minimal overlap."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Consistent APIs"],": Standardize communication interfaces between micro frontends for smooth integration."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Shared Design System"],": Use a common design system to ensure visual consistency."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Monitoring and Observability"],": Implement thorough monitoring and logging to manage complex systems effectively."]],["h2",{"id":"pros-and-cons-analysis"},["strong",{},"Pros and Cons Analysis"]],["p",{},["strong",{},"Pros:"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Improved Development Speed"],": Independent teams can work simultaneously on different features without interference."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Better Fault Isolation"],": Issues in one micro frontend don''t affect others, enhancing system reliability."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Tech Stack Flexibility"],": Teams can adopt new technologies without complete system overhaul."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Simplified Testing"],": Smaller, isolated codebases are easier to test and maintain."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Incremental Updates"],": Features can be updated or replaced without affecting the entire application."]],["p",{},["strong",{},"Cons:"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Initial Setup Complexity"],": Setting up the infrastructure and deployment pipeline requires significant effort."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Bundle Size Management"],": Multiple frameworks can lead to duplicate dependencies and larger bundle sizes."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Learning Curve"],": Teams need to understand distributed systems and cross-team collaboration patterns."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Development Overhead"],": Managing multiple repositories and build processes increases operational complexity."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Integration Testing Challenges"],": Testing interactions between micro frontends requires additional effort and tooling."]],["h2",{"id":"conclusion"},["strong",{},"Conclusion"]],["p",{},"Micro frontend architecture offers a powerful approach to building scalable and maintainable applications. While it brings benefits like faster development and flexible technology choices, it also presents challenges that require careful planning. As web development evolves, micro frontends provide organizations with an effective way to manage complexity and speed up development."]],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"introduction","depth":2,"text":"Introduction"},{"id":"core-principles","depth":2,"text":"Core Principles"},{"id":"advantages","depth":2,"text":"Advantages"},{"id":"challenges","depth":2,"text":"Challenges"},{"id":"use-cases","depth":2,"text":"Use Cases"},{"id":"best-practices","depth":2,"text":"Best Practices"},{"id":"pros-and-cons-analysis","depth":2,"text":"Pros and Cons Analysis"},{"id":"conclusion","depth":2,"text":"Conclusion"}]}}','2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z','By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME','md','https://images.pexels.com/photos/11813187/pexels-photo-11813187.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1','{}',4,'true','/blog/micro-frontend-architecture','{"title":"[Javascript][January 2025] - Micro Frontend Architecture","description":"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"}','blog/006.micro-frontend-architecture','7AE6S3PzQsJToWKr4m1MnD_ykqWojns7o8pWHMInFbw');
INSERT INTO "_content_blog" VALUES('blog/blog/007.prerendering-and-hydration-in-vuejs.md','[Vue][January 2025] - Pre-rendering and Hydration in Vue.js','{"name":"Sean Erick C. Ramones","avatar":{"src":"avatars/profile-image-1.png","alt":"Sean Erick C. Ramones"}}','{"type":"minimark","value":[["h1",{"id":"vuejanuary-2025-pre-rendering-and-hydration-in-vuejs"},"[Vue]",["span",{},"January 2025"]," - Pre-rendering and Hydration in Vue.js"],["p",{},["em",{},"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"]],["p",{},["strong",{},"Introduction"],"\nIn the quest for faster web applications and better user experiences, pre-rendering and hydration have become essential techniques in modern web development. Vue.js, a progressive JavaScript framework, supports these strategies to improve page load times, enhance SEO, and deliver seamless interactivity. This report delves into the concepts of pre-rendering and hydration, their benefits, challenges, and how they work in Vue.js applications."],["p",{},["strong",{},"2. What is Hydration?"],"\nHydration is the process where Vue.js takes the static HTML generated by pre-rendering and \"hydrates\" it by attaching the client-side JavaScript to make the page interactive. This involves Vue scanning the existing DOM and binding it to Vue instances without re-rendering the entire page."],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Steps in Hydration"],":",["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Initial Render"],": The static HTML is rendered quickly on the client side."],["li",{},["strong",{},"JavaScript Execution"],": Vue''s client-side JavaScript loads and initializes."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Hydration Process"],": Vue attaches event listeners and binds data to the existing HTML, making the page fully interactive."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Example"],":\nA Vue component pre-rendered as static HTML will be hydrated as follows:",["pre",{"className":"language-html shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"<!-- Static HTML generated by prerendering -->\n<div id=\"app\">\n  <h1>Welcome to Vue.js</h1>\n</div>\n\n<!-- Vue.js hydrating the HTML -->\n<script src=\"main.js\"></script>\n","language":"html","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{"class":"sHwdD"},"<!-- Static HTML generated by prerendering -->\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"<"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"div"],["span",{"class":"spNyl"}," id"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"="],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"\""],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"app"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"\""],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},">\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"  <"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"h1"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},">"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"Welcome to Vue.js"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"</"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"h1"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},">\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":4},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"</"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"div"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},">\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":5},["span",{"emptyLinePlaceholder":true},"\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":6},["span",{"class":"sHwdD"},"<!-- Vue.js hydrating the HTML -->\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":7},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"<"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"script"],["span",{"class":"spNyl"}," src"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"="],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"\""],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"main.js"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"\""],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"></"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"script"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},">\n"]]]]]],["hr",{}],["p",{},["strong",{},"3. Benefits of Pre-rendering and Hydration"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Improved Performance"],": Users experience faster load times since the static HTML is displayed immediately."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Better SEO"],": Pre-rendered HTML is easier for search engines to crawl, improving visibility and ranking."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Enhanced User Experience"],": Hydration adds interactivity seamlessly, ensuring users can interact with the page without delay."]],["hr",{}],["p",{},["strong",{},"4. Challenges and Considerations"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Hydration Mismatches"],": If the pre-rendered HTML does not match the virtual DOM generated by Vue, hydration errors or warnings may occur. Ensuring consistency between the server-rendered output and client-side Vue components is crucial."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Increased Complexity"],": Implementing pre-rendering and hydration adds complexity to the development workflow, requiring careful consideration of both static content and dynamic interactivity."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Payload Size"],": While pre-rendering reduces initial load times, the client still needs to download and execute JavaScript for hydration, which can affect performance on slower networks or devices."]],["hr",{}],["p",{},["strong",{},"5. Tools Supporting Pre-rendering and Hydration"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Vue CLI"],": Offers plugins and configurations to facilitate pre-rendering and manage hydration seamlessly."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Nuxt.js"],": Provides built-in support for both server-side rendering (SSR) and static site generation (SSG), making it easier to implement pre-rendering and hydration in Vue.js applications."]],["hr",{}],["p",{},["strong",{},"6. Best Practices"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Optimize Assets"],": Minimize the size of JavaScript bundles to reduce the payload that needs to be hydrated."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Monitor Performance"],": Use tools like Lighthouse to audit the performance of your Vue.js application and identify areas for improvement."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Test for Consistency"],": Ensure that the static HTML and the hydrated application behave consistently to avoid mismatches and errors."]],["hr",{}],["p",{},["strong",{},"Conclusion"],"\nPre-rendering and hydration are powerful techniques in Vue.js that can significantly enhance the performance and user experience of web applications. By generating static HTML at build time and seamlessly attaching interactivity through hydration, developers can deliver fast, responsive, and SEO-friendly applications. While there are challenges to consider, the benefits of implementing these strategies make them an essential part of modern Vue.js development."],["style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sHwdD, html code.shiki .sHwdD{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-light-font-style:italic;--shiki-default:#546E7A;--shiki-default-font-style:italic;--shiki-dark:#676E95;--shiki-dark-font-style:italic}html pre.shiki code .sMK4o, html code.shiki .sMK4o{--shiki-light:#39ADB5;--shiki-default:#89DDFF;--shiki-dark:#89DDFF}html pre.shiki code .swJcz, html code.shiki .swJcz{--shiki-light:#E53935;--shiki-default:#F07178;--shiki-dark:#F07178}html pre.shiki code .spNyl, html code.shiki .spNyl{--shiki-light:#9C3EDA;--shiki-default:#C792EA;--shiki-dark:#C792EA}html pre.shiki code .sfazB, html code.shiki .sfazB{--shiki-light:#91B859;--shiki-default:#C3E88D;--shiki-dark:#C3E88D}html pre.shiki code .sTEyZ, html code.shiki .sTEyZ{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-default:#EEFFFF;--shiki-dark:#BABED8}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration);}html.dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration);}"]],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[]}}','2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z','By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME','md','https://images.pexels.com/photos/270404/pexels-photo-270404.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1','{}',3,'true','/blog/prerendering-and-hydration-in-vuejs','{"title":"[Vue][January 2025] - Pre-rendering and Hydration in Vue.js","description":"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"}','blog/007.prerendering-and-hydration-in-vuejs','4zb7INjm2K6whgZ4bTeVR95x7Tf05xpUDwdjxA59--w');
INSERT INTO "_content_blog" VALUES('blog/blog/009.vue-js-and-progressive-web-apps.md','[Vue][February 2025] - Vue.js and Progressive Web Apps (PWA) – Enhancing Web Experiences','{"name":"Sean Erick C. Ramones","avatar":{"src":"avatars/profile-image-1.png","alt":"Sean Erick C. Ramones"}}','{"type":"minimark","value":[["h1",{"id":"vuefebruary-2025-vuejs-and-progressive-web-apps-pwa-enhancing-web-experiences"},"[Vue]",["span",{},"February 2025"]," - Vue.js and Progressive Web Apps (PWA) – Enhancing Web Experiences"],["p",{},["em",{},"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"]],["h2",{"id":"introduction"},"Introduction"],["p",{},"Progressive Web Apps (PWAs) have transformed the way users interact with web applications by delivering fast, reliable, and engaging experiences. With Vue.js, developers can build PWAs seamlessly, leveraging its simplicity and powerful ecosystem. This report explores how Vue.js facilitates PWA development, key benefits, and considerations for when PWA might not be the best choice for an application."],["h2",{"id":"benefits-of-vue-powered-pwas"},"Benefits of Vue-powered PWAs"],["h3",{"id":"enhanced-performance"},"Enhanced Performance"],["ul",{},["li",{},"PWAs load quickly due to caching and resource preloading, reducing wait times and improving user experience."],["li",{},"Vue''s reactivity system ensures efficient rendering, contributing to smooth interactions and responsiveness."]],["h3",{"id":"offline-availability"},"Offline Availability"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Users can access content even when offline, thanks to cached assets and Service Workers that store data locally."],["li",{},"This is especially beneficial for applications that provide reading content, e-commerce catalogs, or progressive form submissions."]],["h3",{"id":"increased-engagement"},"Increased Engagement"],["ul",{},["li",{},"PWAs can send push notifications, keeping users informed and encouraging them to return to the app."],["li",{},"Installable PWAs make it easier for users to access the app without needing an app store download."]],["h3",{"id":"cross-platform-compatibility"},"Cross-Platform Compatibility"],["ul",{},["li",{},"PWAs work seamlessly on various devices, whether mobile, tablet, or desktop, with a responsive design that adapts to different screen sizes."]],["h3",{"id":"reduced-development-cost"},"Reduced Development Cost"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Eliminates the need for developing separate native apps for iOS and Android."],["li",{},"A single codebase reduces maintenance and development effort, making updates easier and faster to deploy."]],["h3",{"id":"seo-and-discoverability"},"SEO and Discoverability"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Unlike native apps, PWAs can be indexed by search engines, making them more discoverable through organic search results."],["li",{},"This helps businesses gain more visibility and attract a broader audience."]],["hr",{}],["h2",{"id":"when-you-might-not-want-to-use-a-pwa"},"When You Might NOT Want to Use a PWA"],["p",{},"While PWAs offer many advantages, there are scenarios where they might not be the best choice:"],["h3",{"id":"limited-access-to-native-device-features"},"Limited Access to Native Device Features"],["ul",{},["li",{},"PWAs have restricted access to certain native device capabilities such as Bluetooth, advanced camera controls, and biometric authentication."],["li",{},"If your application requires deep system integration, a native app may be a better fit."]],["h3",{"id":"performance-constraints-for-complex-applications"},"Performance Constraints for Complex Applications"],["ul",{},["li",{},"PWAs may struggle with high-performance applications such as intensive gaming, AR/VR experiences, or apps that require heavy real-time processing."],["li",{},"Native apps can leverage system resources more efficiently for such use cases."]],["h3",{"id":"app-store-presence"},"App Store Presence"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Some businesses rely on app stores for distribution and monetization, which can be a limitation for PWAs."],["li",{},"While some platforms like Microsoft and Google allow PWAs in their stores, Apple has more restrictive policies."]],["h3",{"id":"security-and-privacy-considerations"},"Security and Privacy Considerations"],["ul",{},["li",{},"While PWAs are served over HTTPS, they are still web-based and may not offer the same level of security as a native app, especially for handling highly sensitive data."]],["h3",{"id":"user-expectations"},"User Expectations"],["ul",{},["li",{},"If your target audience expects an app-store experience with native performance and deep integration, they may be less inclined to use a PWA."],["li",{},"Certain demographics, such as enterprise users, may prefer downloadable software over browser-based applications."]],["hr",{}],["h2",{"id":"how-to-use-vue-with-pwa"},"How to Use Vue with PWA"],["p",{},"Vue simplifies PWA implementation with its built-in PWA plugin. To get started, you can use Vue CLI to create a new project and add PWA support with the following command:"],["pre",{"className":"language-markdown shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"vue create my-vue-pwa\ncd my-vue-pwa\nvue add pwa\n","language":"markdown","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{},"vue create my-vue-pwa\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{},"cd my-vue-pwa\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{},"vue add pwa\n"]]]],["p",{},"This will configure the necessary Service Worker, Web App Manifest, and caching strategies. For a more detailed guide, refer to the official Vue PWA documentation: ",["a",{"href":"https://cli.vuejs.org/core-plugins/pwa.html","rel":["nofollow"]},"Vue PWA Plugin"],"."],["hr",{}],["h2",{"id":"conclusion"},"Conclusion"],["p",{},"Vue.js simplifies PWA development with its intuitive framework and rich ecosystem. By leveraging Vue CLI, Service Workers, Web App Manifests, and modern caching strategies, developers can build high-performance, offline-ready applications."],["p",{},"However, while PWAs offer numerous benefits such as improved performance, offline capabilities, and cost efficiency, they are not a one-size-fits-all solution. Developers should carefully evaluate their application''s requirements, user expectations, and technical constraints before adopting a PWA approach."],["style",{},"html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration);}html.dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dark-text-decoration);}"]],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"introduction","depth":2,"text":"Introduction"},{"id":"benefits-of-vue-powered-pwas","depth":2,"text":"Benefits of Vue-powered PWAs","children":[{"id":"enhanced-performance","depth":3,"text":"Enhanced Performance"},{"id":"offline-availability","depth":3,"text":"Offline Availability"},{"id":"increased-engagement","depth":3,"text":"Increased Engagement"},{"id":"cross-platform-compatibility","depth":3,"text":"Cross-Platform Compatibility"},{"id":"reduced-development-cost","depth":3,"text":"Reduced Development Cost"},{"id":"seo-and-discoverability","depth":3,"text":"SEO and Discoverability"}]},{"id":"when-you-might-not-want-to-use-a-pwa","depth":2,"text":"When You Might NOT Want to Use a PWA","children":[{"id":"limited-access-to-native-device-features","depth":3,"text":"Limited Access to Native Device Features"},{"id":"performance-constraints-for-complex-applications","depth":3,"text":"Performance Constraints for Complex Applications"},{"id":"app-store-presence","depth":3,"text":"App Store Presence"},{"id":"security-and-privacy-considerations","depth":3,"text":"Security and Privacy Considerations"},{"id":"user-expectations","depth":3,"text":"User Expectations"}]},{"id":"how-to-use-vue-with-pwa","depth":2,"text":"How to Use Vue with PWA"},{"id":"conclusion","depth":2,"text":"Conclusion"}]}}','2025-02-01T00:00:00.000Z','By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME','md','https://images.pexels.com/photos/109371/pexels-photo-109371.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1','{}',3,'true','/blog/vue-js-and-progressive-web-apps','{"title":"[Vue][February 2025] - Vue.js and Progressive Web Apps (PWA) – Enhancing Web Experiences","description":"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypeScript SME"}','blog/009.vue-js-and-progressive-web-apps','ai7eKV1zp9xXeG9uqV4QiLPGoFxirBTWnhDaOwSmit0');
INSERT INTO "_content_blog" VALUES('blog/blog/010.moving-from-a-traditional-api-to-serverless.md','[Javascript][March 2025] - Moving from a Traditional Node.js CRUD API to Serverless Architecture—A Deep Dive','{"name":"Sean Erick C. Ramones","avatar":{"src":"avatars/profile-image-1.png","alt":"Sean Erick C. Ramones"}}','{"type":"minimark","value":[["h1",{"id":"javascriptmarch-2025-moving-from-a-traditional-nodejs-crud-api-to-serverless-architecturea-deep-dive"},"[Javascript]",["span",{},"March 2025"]," - Moving from a Traditional Node.js CRUD API to Serverless Architecture—A Deep Dive"],["p",{},["em",{},"By Sean Erick C. Ramones, Vue SME | JavaScript/TypScript SME"]],["h3",{"id":"introduction"},["strong",{},"Introduction"]],["p",{},"Serverless architecture is transforming web development by removing server management complexities, letting developers focus purely on code. While traditional Node.js applications require dedicated servers, serverless functions enable deployment of APIs that scale automatically, lower costs, and enhance performance. This report examines the core differences between traditional Node.js CRUD APIs and serverless APIs, providing guidance on migration strategies, best practices, and key considerations."],["h3",{"id":"what-is-serverless-architecture"},["strong",{},"What is Serverless Architecture?"]],["p",{},"Serverless architecture eliminates server management by running code on demand in ",["strong",{},"serverless functions"],". These functions are stateless, event-driven, and execute in response to HTTP requests, database triggers, or other events. Popular platforms include:"],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"AWS Lambda"]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Vercel Functions"]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Netlify Functions"]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Cloudflare Workers"]]],["p",{},"In a serverless setup, instead of maintaining a single long-running server, you deploy isolated functions that handle specific tasks, such as CRUD operations."],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"migrating-a-nodejs-crud-api-to-serverless"},["strong",{},"Migrating a Node.js CRUD API to Serverless"]],["p",{},"Let''s explore how to convert the traditional CRUD API example into a serverless architecture using ",["strong",{},"serverless functions"],"."],["h3",{"id":"step-1-create-serverless-functions"},["strong",{},"Step 1: Create Serverless Functions"]],["p",{},"For each CRUD operation, create separate serverless functions. Example folder structure for Netlify:"],["pre",{"className":["language-text"],"code":"/netlify/functions\n  └── getUsers.js\n  └── createUser.js\n  └── updateUser.js\n  └── deleteUser.j\n","language":"text"},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},"/netlify/functions\n  └── getUsers.js\n  └── createUser.js\n  └── updateUser.js\n  └── deleteUser.j\n"]],["p",{},"Each file exports an asynchronous handler function:"],["p",{},["strong",{},["code",{},"getUsers.js"],":"]],["pre",{"className":"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"exports.handler = async (event, context) => {\n  // Simulate fetching users from a database\n  const users = [{ id: 1, name: ''Alice'' }, { id: 2, name: ''Bob'' }];\n  return {\n    statusCode: 200,\n    body: JSON.stringify(users),\n  };\n};\n","language":"jsx","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"exports."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"handler"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ="],["span",{"class":"spNyl"}," async"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ("],["span",{"class":"sHdIc"},"event"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"sHdIc"}," context"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},")"],["span",{"class":"spNyl"}," =>"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{"class":"sHwdD"},"  // Simulate fetching users from a database\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{"class":"spNyl"},"  const"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," users"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ="],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," ["],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"{"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," id"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sbssI"}," 1"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," name"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"Alice"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," },"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," id"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sbssI"}," 2"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," name"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"Bob"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," }"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"]"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":4},["span",{"class":"s7zQu"},"  return"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":5},["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"    statusCode"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sbssI"}," 200"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},",\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":6},["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"    body"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," JSON"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"stringify"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"("],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"users"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},",\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":7},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"  };\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":8},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"};\n"]]]],["p",{},["strong",{},["code",{},"createUser.js"],":"]],["pre",{"className":"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight","code":"exports.handler = async (event, context) => {\n  const newUser = JSON.parse(event.body);\n  // Simulate saving to a database\n  return {\n    statusCode: 201,\n    body: JSON.stringify({ message: ''User created'', user: newUser }),\n  };\n};\n","language":"jsx","meta":"","style":""},["code",{"__ignoreMap":""},["span",{"class":"line","line":1},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"exports."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"handler"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ="],["span",{"class":"spNyl"}," async"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ("],["span",{"class":"sHdIc"},"event"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"sHdIc"}," context"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},")"],["span",{"class":"spNyl"}," =>"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":2},["span",{"class":"spNyl"},"  const"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," newUser"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ="],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," JSON"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"parse"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"("],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"event"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"},"body"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},";\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":3},["span",{"class":"sHwdD"},"  // Simulate saving to a database\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":4},["span",{"class":"s7zQu"},"  return"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," {\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":5},["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"    statusCode"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sbssI"}," 201"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},",\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":6},["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"    body"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," JSON"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"."],["span",{"class":"s2Zo4"},"stringify"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},"("],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"{"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," message"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," ''"],["span",{"class":"sfazB"},"User created"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"''"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},","],["span",{"class":"swJcz"}," user"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},":"],["span",{"class":"sTEyZ"}," newUser"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"}," }"],["span",{"class":"swJcz"},")"],["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},",\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":7},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"  };\n"]],["span",{"class":"line","line":8},["span",{"class":"sMK4o"},"};\n"]]]],["h3",{"id":"step-2-deploy-the-functions"},["strong",{},"Step 2: Deploy the Functions"]],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Netlify:"]," Functions in the ",["code",{},"/netlify/functions"]," folder are automatically deployed as serverless functions."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Vercel:"]," Place functions in the ",["code",{},"/api"]," folder for automatic deployment."],["li",{},["strong",{},"AWS Lambda:"]," Use frameworks like ",["strong",{},"Serverless Framework"]," or ",["strong",{},"AWS SAM"]," to deploy Lambda functions."]],["h3",{"id":"step-3-testing-the-serverless-api"},["strong",{},"Step 3: Testing the Serverless API"]],["p",{},"Once deployed, each function is accessible as an individual endpoint:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"GET ",["code",{},"/api/getUsers"]],["li",{},"POST ",["code",{},"/api/createUser"]],["li",{},"PUT ",["code",{},"/api/updateUser"]],["li",{},"DELETE ",["code",{},"/api/deleteUser"]]],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"benefits-of-serverless-crud-apis"},["strong",{},"Benefits of Serverless CRUD APIs"]],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Automatic Scaling"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Serverless functions scale automatically based on incoming requests, eliminating the need for load balancers or additional servers."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Reduced Costs"],["ul",{},["li",{},"You only pay for actual compute time used, making serverless particularly cost-effective for apps with variable or low traffic."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Faster Time to Deploy"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Deploying serverless functions is as simple as pushing code to platforms like Netlify or Vercel."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Improved Resilience"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Since functions are isolated and stateless, failures are contained to individual functions."]]]],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"challenges-and-trade-offs"},["strong",{},"Challenges and Trade-Offs"]],["p",{},"While serverless architecture offers numerous benefits, it comes with specific challenges:"],["ol",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Cold Starts"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Initial requests after periods of inactivity may be slower due to function \"wake-up\" time—known as a ",["strong",{},"cold start"],". Platforms like Cloudflare Workers help minimize this issue."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Execution Time Limits"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Serverless functions typically have execution limits (e.g., 10 seconds on Netlify). Longer tasks may need to be split or handled asynchronously."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Limited State Persistence"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Serverless functions are stateless and can''t retain in-memory data between requests. External services (databases or caches) are needed for state management."]]],["li",{},["strong",{},"Debugging and Monitoring"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Debugging distributed serverless functions requires specialized tools like AWS CloudWatch, Vercel Analytics, or Sentry for effective monitoring."]]]],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"when-to-use-serverless-for-crud-apis"},["strong",{},"When to Use Serverless for CRUD APIs"]],["p",{},"Serverless CRUD APIs excel in these scenarios:"],["ul",{},["li",{},["strong",{},"Low-Traffic or Burst Traffic Apps:"]," Cost-effective scaling and minimal idle costs make serverless ideal for unpredictable traffic patterns."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Prototypes and MVPs:"]," Quick deployment and automatic scaling let you focus on feature development rather than infrastructure."],["li",{},["strong",{},"Global Applications:"]," Edge-deployed functions deliver content with minimal latency worldwide."]],["p",{},"However, traditional server-based approaches may be more suitable for applications with consistent high traffic, strict latency requirements, or complex long-running processes."],["hr",{}],["h3",{"id":"conclusion"},["strong",{},"Conclusion"]],["p",{},"Migrating from a traditional Node.js CRUD API to serverless architecture offers compelling benefits in scalability, cost efficiency, and deployment speed. Breaking applications into modular, stateless functions enables more resilient and flexible systems. While it''s crucial to consider trade-offs and prepare for challenges like cold starts, proper optimization can maximize serverless benefits."],["p",{},"With platforms like Netlify, Vercel, and AWS Lambda making the transition straightforward, serverless architecture has become an attractive choice for modern web development."],["h3",{"id":"bonus-smes-afterthoughts"},"Bonus: SME''s Afterthoughts"],["p",{},"SME Notes: In the Preesh project, we currently use Netlify Edge functions to handle API responses for OpenAI text generation, while using Nitro event handlers to communicate with our database (Supabase—a serverless DB with its own serverless edge functions). We''re now transitioning to NuxtHub, a more centralized platform that leverages Cloudflare services for database operations and file storage. This serverless approach significantly accelerates development since we don''t need to worry about server configuration and setup."],["style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sMK4o, html code.shiki .sMK4o{--shiki-light:#39ADB5;--shiki-default:#89DDFF;--shiki-dark:#89DDFF}html pre.shiki code .s2Zo4, html code.shiki .s2Zo4{--shiki-light:#6182B8;--shiki-default:#82AAFF;--shiki-dark:#82AAFF}html pre.shiki code .spNyl, html code.shiki .spNyl{--shiki-light:#9C3EDA;--shiki-default:#C792EA;--shiki-dark:#C792EA}html pre.shiki code .sHdIc, html code.shiki .sHdIc{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-light-font-style:italic;--shiki-default:#EEFFFF;--shiki-default-font-style:italic;--shiki-dark:#BABED8;--shiki-dark-font-style:italic}html pre.shiki code .sHwdD, html code.shiki .sHwdD{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-light-font-style:italic;--shiki-default:#546E7A;--shiki-default-font-style:italic;--shiki-dark:#676E95;--shiki-dark-font-style:italic}html pre.shiki code .sTEyZ, html code.shiki .sTEyZ{--shiki-light:#90A4AE;--shiki-default:#EEFFFF;--shiki-dark:#BABED8}html pre.shiki co